desktop-defaults (0.10.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * take care not to break the su -c () subshell in fll-gnome.init.
  * desktop-defaults-kde
    - clean up XDG desktop file.
    - do the big code movement to factor out do_start() from
      fll-kde-desktop.init to preseed-user-home-kde, functionally incomplete.
    - remove chown calls, we're running as the specified user now and do no
      longer have access to super user capabilities.
    - switch install calls to mkdir/ cp.
    - we're now running as user, ${FLL_LIVE_USER_HOME} --> ${HOME}.
    - install and start preseed-user-home-kde.
    - source desktop-defaults.
    - set default umask.
    - set -e, actually show display the exit state.
    - move fll-desktop-func to /usr/share/desktop-defaults-common/.
    - rework fll-desktop-func/ cp_desktop_defaults_from() to work as user.
    - re-add environment configuration.
    - depend on kwin, no need to check it.
  * move fll-desktop-func into common subdirectory.
  * add preseed-user-home-foo stubs for other desktop environments.
  * desktop-defaults-common
    - do the big code movement to factor out do_start() from
      fll-common-desktop.init to preseed-user-home-common, functionally
      incomplete.
    - we're now running as user, ${FLL_LIVE_USER_HOME} --> ${HOME}.
    - switch install calls to mkdir/ cp.
    - remove chown calls, we're running as the specified user now and do no
      longer have access to super user capabilities.
    - remove sudo calls, we're running as the specified user now and do no
      longer have access to super user capabilities.
    - we need to inherit the cheatcode handling as well.
    - sudo is mandatory, depend on it.
    - really remove obsolete do_start() call.
    - actually install preseed-user-home-common.
    - don't ship empty directories in oour skeleton, create 'em on boot.
    - start update-alternatives as root.
  * desktop-defaults-gnome:
    - remove empty desktop-defaults-gnome.install.
    - re-add environment configuration.
    - do the big code movement to factor out do_start() from
      fll-gnome-desktop.init to preseed-user-home-gnome, functionally
      incomplete.
    - install and start preseed-user-home-kde.
    - remove chown calls, we're running as the specified user now and do no
      longer have access to super user capabilities.
    - switch install calls to mkdir/ cp.
    - stop messing with profiles for root.
    - we're running as user now, su is no longer needed (nor actually
      possible) to call gconftool-2.
    - we need to inherit the cheatcode handling as well.
    - drep-dctrl is no longer needed.
    - fix call to preseed-user-home-gnome.
    - we're now running as user, ${FLL_LIVE_USER_HOME} --> ${HOME}.
  * desktop-defaults-xfce
    - re-add environment configuration.
    - we need to inherit the cheatcode handling as well.
    - depend on xfwm4, no need to check it.
    - do the big code movement to factor out do_start() from
      fll-xfce-desktop.init to preseed-user-home-xfce, functionally incomplete.
    - install and start preseed-user-home-kde.
    - we're now running as user, ${FLL_LIVE_USER_HOME} --> ${HOME}.
    - remove chown calls, we're running as the specified user now and do no
      longer have access to super user capabilities.
    - switch install calls to mkdir/ cp.
    - fix preseed-user-home-xfce invocation.
    - invoke /usr/share/desktop-defaults-xfce/preseed-user-home-xfce.
  * remove "set -e" introduced for debugging, on the release the preseeding
    needs to work on a best efforts basis, errors are still printed to stdout.
  * re-introduce do_start() functions to allow additions in a central place
    easily.
  * match copyrights with reality.
  * hand further maintenance over to the maintainers of each desktop
    environment.

